{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01SKxGR13wYr2wczrY2XFwmT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All verification criteria are satisfied:\n\n| # | Requirement | Result |\n|---|---|---|\n| 1 | Cluster health yellow/green with 5 nodes | ✅ **green**, 5 nodes |\n| 2 | app-data shards on nodes outside original 3 | ✅ all 6 shards on `es-extra-0`/`es-extra-1` |\n| 3 | New nodes have a different allocation attribute | ✅ `node.attr.zone=zoneb` (originals have none) |\n| 4 | `es-cluster` StatefulSet remains at 3 replicas | ✅ untouched at 3 |\n\n## What I did\n\nThe live 3-node cluster was the `es` StatefulSet (es-0/1/2), reachable over HTTPS at `es-http:9200`. The `es-cluster`/`es-transform` StatefulSets were crashlooping distractors I deliberately left alone (and verification #4 explicitly forbids scaling `es-cluster`).\n\n1. **Added 2 data nodes** via a new StatefulSet `es-extra` (2 replicas) that joins the same cluster — same image (8.11.1), certs (`es-http-tls`), password, and `discovery.seed_hosts: [\"es-transport\"]` + `app: elasticsearch` label so the headless service discovers them. They use a separate configmap `es-config-extra` adding **`node.attr.zone: zoneb`**, giving them a distinct allocation attribute from the original nodes (which have no zone attr).\n2. **Created and seeded the `app-data` index** — the precondition had failed to create it (it used plain `http` against this TLS-only cluster), so the index was missing. I created it with `index.routing.allocation.require.zone: zoneb`, forcing all primaries and replicas onto the two new nodes.\n3. **Verified**: green health, 5 nodes, all app-data shards on the new nodes, no impact to `es-cluster`.\n\nNo operators or CRDs were used."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":513,"cache_read_input_tokens":40901,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":513},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"32cf3128-5456-4a32-84d4-7d10f687667d","uuid":"1a221f9b-7019-486a-bf53-834c1f497f54","request_id":"req_011CcAinJhe4QioFSiCvazTw"}
